``` java
 public static boolean verbose() {
 return cVerbose.get();
 }
```
A better approach could be to remove the initialization and test for null:
``` java
public static boolean verbose(){
 Boolean verbose = cVerbose.get();
 return (verbose !
= null) ?
verbose : false;
}
```
